 House of Representatives Speaker Femi Gbajabiamila has said the Soun of Ogbomoso land, Oba Oladunni Ajagungbade III, has been a source of inspiration to his subjects and others. In his statement signed by his Special Adviser on Media and Publicity, Lanre Lasisi, the Speaker said sons and daughters of Ogbomoso land are lucky to have Oba Ajagungbade III as their traditional ruler, who happens to be the longest-serving Soun. Gbajabiamila eulogised the Soun for using his stool to bring development to Ogbomoso land over the years, saying he deserved commendation for his qualitative leadership. He prayed that the Almighty God would continue to keep the Soun in good health and increase him in wisdom for the benefit of the people of Ogbomoso land and beyond.  Minister of Youth and Sports Development Sunday Dare rejoiced with Oba Ajagungbade 111 on the occasion of his 95th birthday anniversary. He described the monarch as “a living legend”, saying he was a selfless and patriotic leader, whose contributions to nation-building were commendable and worthy of emulation. According to the minister, who holds the title of Agbaakin of Ogbomoso, Oba Oyewumi’s reign has been beneficial to Ogbomoso people, Oyo State and Nigeria. He said the monarch used his resources to advance the cause of the people, adding that Ogbomoso and its environs had experienced rapid development under Oba Oyewumi’s watch. 